raph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;">A full grip. The suicide grip is much harder to do properly and is more risky to do. It's also not allowed in professional powerlifting. So just stick to the full grip.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1657110892309" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1657110892309"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Should I wear wrist wraps when benching?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1656945317455" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1656945317455"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Wrist wraps can be very helpful if you're struggling with your bench press wrist position or if your wrist joints are in some pain. Make sure, however, that you don't become reliant on the wrist wraps. The target is to bench properly without them. If you decide to use wrist wraps I recommend <a href="https://www.amazon.com/WARM-BODY-COLD-MIND-Weightlifting/dp/B08LQPJLJY?tag=bench-press-wrist-position-20" class="" target="_blank">these ones</a>.</p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1668074602216" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1668074602216" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_m